 for those that don't spec all the way to 50 DW, but for anyone else I can't see the point of using it.  Now, if they changed it so that bleeds could stack (even if just from different styles) then it would be worth putting it back.  As it stands now though I use DS if I want them to bleed, if I parry I use Reflection and follow it up with Hypno if I don't think my target is stun immune.  Reflection will do similar damage for less endo and I don't get the message telling me that my target already has the bleed effect. <p>Nirala MistyGloomfortehWIN<br>
