<br>
There is no point using Flank/DT combo at any time including if you are perpetually fighting people on their side in every single engagement. The no-hit bonus is the biggest reason besides the difficulty in actually positioning yourself properly. The benefit is hardly noticeable. This combo isn't nearly as effective as the rear positional combo in the LA line or the side postional stun combo in the CD line or the side postional stun in the Savage HTH line. It boils down to the fact that the damage output from this combo, even improved, is still only comparable to other combos that are much easier to execute. I suggest either adding in a smal duration stun component or some kind of damage proc to this combo along with atleast a small to-hit bonus on the opener.<br>
<br>
