<br>
Dual Shadows - this style works really well now.The bleed is good. The damage is so-so (kind of low for a level 50 style) and luckily most people fight you from the front in RvR.  The defense modifier has to go. This is not like the LW Anhillation style where you get a 9 second stun.  We can't run around and stun a whole enemy group like Champs and Heros can. We don't get a large proc like Reavers get on Leviathian. No need for defense decrease at all.  There should be no debate that Dual Shadows should be greater than Amyth + Diamond but its not. <br>
<br>
Dark Tendrils - this style is ok to have your bar for PvE fighting only. In RvR you will always use the Relflection/HD combo with a backup of Dual Shadows or Amyth. The battles go so fast that 1 stun is all your need before you take down a person. In mob fighting, you can do a Ref/HD and still have tons of parries afterwards which you can us Tendrils on.  This style doesn't stay on my hot bar at all.<br>
<br>
Shadows Edge/Penumbra - not a good combo. Better off using Blackslash twice as it has better damage and a higher chance to hit both times.<br>
